headlines.description: — Jared McCain scored 30 points and Tyrese Maxey added 26 as the Philadelphia 76ers snapped a five-game losing streak with a 113-98 win over the Brooklyn Nets in an NBA Cup game Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: McCain and Maxey help the 76ers rally to beat the Nets 113-98 and snap 5-game losing streak

headlines.description: — Jaylen Brown scored 31 points, and the Boston Celtics overcame an off night for Jayson Tatum to beat the Washington Wizards 108-96 in the NBA Cup on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brown scores 31 points to help the Celtics outlast the Wizards 108-96 for a key NBA Cup victory

events.name: Golden State Warriors at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Andrew Wiggins scored 30 points and the Golden State Warriors secured a knockout round spot in the NBA Cup with a 112-108 victory over the reeling New Orleans Pelicans on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wiggins scores 30, Warriors win their NBA Cup group with a 112-108 triumph over the Pelicans

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 37 points, 11 assists and 10 rebounds for his second triple-double in his last four games, and the Milwaukee Bucks beat the Indiana Pacers 129-117 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo gets triple-double as surging Bucks beat slumping Pacers 129-117 in NBA Cup play

headlines.description: — Zach LaVine scored 26 points, Ayo Dosunmu and Coby White each had 20 and the Chicago Bulls beat the Atlanta Hawks 136-122 on Friday night in an NBA Cup game.
headlines.shortLinkText: LaVine, Dosunmu and White power the Bulls to a 136-122 win over the Hawks

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Dillon Brooks scored a season-high 28 points and led the Houston Rockets to a 116-88 win over the Portland Trail Blazers in an NBA Cup game on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dillon Brooks scores a season-high 28 to lead the Rockets past the Trail Blazers 116-88

headlines.description: — Naji Marshall scored a career-high 26 points, P.J. Washington had 22 points and 13 rebounds, and the Dallas Mavericks recovered after blowing a 24-point lead to beat the Denver Nuggets 123-120 on Friday night in an NBA Cup game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mavericks recover after losing 24-point lead, overcome Jokic's triple-double to beat Nuggets 123-120
